# Company research quality (owner preference)

When adding or refreshing rows in `data/companies.json`, follow `.playbook/07_RESEARCH_GUIDE.md`
(**Careers URL rules** and **M&A, rebrand, and duplicate employers**).

## Hard rules

1. **`careersUrl`** ‚Äî employer-owned only (company careers/jobs page or their ATS). Never Cutshort,
   Foundit, Naukri, Shine, Indeed, LinkedIn `/jobs`, or other job boards.
2. **Job boards** ‚Äî OK in `hiringEvidence` / `jobSearchUrl` only.
3. **M&A / rebrand** ‚Äî do not add a child brand if the parent is already listed (e.g. Zorang‚ÜíGSPANN,
   Lister Digital‚ÜíBounteous). Update or keep the surviving row; note the former name in `notes` if useful.
4. **No careers page** ‚Äî do not publish the row; park the candidate for owner review instead of using a
   board URL as `careersUrl`.

## Filter data (accuracy is a hard rule ‚Äî double-check existing + new)

5. **`locations`** ‚Äî array of `{city?, country}` covering **all countries the employer hires in + the major city
   hub(s) per country** (not India-only, not every tiny office). `hq` is the global HQ and is often NOT the India
   hiring city ‚Äî research real offices, do not copy `hq`. `country` required per entry; `city` optional. Keep
   India cities complete (audience is India-based) and list the main global hubs elsewhere.
   **Anti-pattern:** do not ship India-only `locations` for a global SI/agency/GCC (Infosys, TCS, Wipro, Globant,
   Dentsu, etc.) ‚Äî always add HQ country + 1‚Äì2 other major hubs when evidenced. India-only is OK only for
   India-HQ product companies / India-only agencies (CEAT, Maruti, Air India, Happiest Minds, TO THE NEW).
6. **`remote`** ‚Äî `true` only with evidence of remote hiring relevant to India candidates.
7. **`noticePolicy`** ‚Äî one of `immediate` / `30d` / `60d` / `90d` / `flexible-long`; set **only when a
   posting/careers page states or implies it**, else omit (`flexible-long` = long notice ok or range unclear).
8. **`hiringActive`** ‚Äî set `true` when evidence shows a **frequent (~monthly or more)** AEM/DXP hiring cadence
   (multiple distinct recent postings, or a careers page consistently showing AEM reqs). Not "open now"; omit
   when occasional/one-off or unknown. Never guess.
9. **`products`** ‚Äî must match what the employer actually works on. Verify against case studies / postings and
   **expand to every evidenced Adobe product + remove any tag with no evidence**. Wrong/understated product tags
   irritate users.
10. **`notes`** ‚Äî shown in the company detail UI. Write for job seekers only. Never put research jargon in
    `notes` (`DR-xxx`, ‚ÄúTier N BuiltWith‚Äù, ‚Äúupgrade Evidence‚Äù, agent TODO language). Put internal research
    labels in session notes or archive manifests, not in published `notes`.

## Link validity

- Every `careersUrl` must resolve (2xx, redirects that still land on the employer are OK). Run
  `npm run check-links` (or `node scripts/verify-links.js`) after batches; fix `dead` (404/DNS) links,
  keep `blocked` (anti-bot) after a manual browser check.

## Before batch append

- Scan existing `companies.json` ids/names for parent brands.
- After edits: `node scripts/verify-companies.js`; run `npm run prerender` when counts or hero stats change.
